<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>About Ciphry</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/CSS/main.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/CSS/variables.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/CSS/register.css" />
    <!--FONT FAMILY-->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,100;0,200;0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;0,800;0,900;1,100;1,200;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,600;1,700;1,800;1,900&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: var(--font-family--);
        background-color: var(--White--);
        color: var(--Black--);
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        line-height: 1.7;
        overflow-x: scroll;
      }
      html,
      body {
        height: auto;
        min-height: 100vh;
        overflow-y: auto;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      main {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 60px auto 80px;
        padding: 0 24px;
      }

      h1,
      h2,
      h3 {
        color: var(--Blue--);
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        margin-bottom: 0.4em;
        line-height: 1.2;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 3.2rem;
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 2.1rem;
        margin-top: 2.5em;
        border-bottom: 3px solid var(--Blue--);
        padding-bottom: 0.3em;
      }
      h3 {
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        margin-top: 1.8em;
        margin-bottom: 0.25em;
      }

      p {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.3em;
        color: var(--Black--);
      }

      blockquote {
        font-style: italic;
        padding-left: 1.2em;
        margin-left: 0;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--Blue--);
        color: var(--Blue--);
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.6em;
        background: rgba(0, 72, 255, 0.06);
        border-radius: 6px;
      }

      ul {
        margin-left: 1.3em;
        margin-bottom: 1.6em;
        color: var(--Black--);
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        list-style-type: disc;
      }

      ul li {
        margin-bottom: 0.75em;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }

      footer {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 40px 12px;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--Black--);
        border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
        margin-top: 60px;
        font-style: italic;
      }

      @media (max-width: 640px) {
        main {
          margin: 30px 18px 50px;
        }
        h1 {
          font-size: 2.4rem;
        }
        h2 {
          font-size: 1.8rem;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>About Ciphry</h1>

      <section>
        <h2>Mission</h2>
        <blockquote>
          To create a safe, honest space where emotions can be expressed without
          judgment, identity can shift freely, and AI understands the human
          behind the words.
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          Ciphry exists to <strong>restore meaning to expression</strong> in a
          world where social media rewards performance over truth. It’s not
          about going viral. It’s about feeling heard — even when silent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Vision / Goal</h2>
        <blockquote>
          Build an emotionally intelligent digital space that empowers
          self-expression, self-awareness, and human connection through
          anonymity, AI, and emotional resonance.
        </blockquote>
        <ul>
          <li>Normalize emotional expression — not hide it.</li>
          <li>Replace toxic performance culture with honest storytelling.</li>
          <li>
            Use AI to help people understand themselves, not manipulate them.
          </li>
          <li>
            Give users tools to track, reflect, and grow emotionally — all
            privately.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What Makes Ciphry Unique</h2>
        <h3>1. Emotion First, Not Popularity</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>No likes. No follower counts.</li>
          <li>What matters is <em>how it feels</em>, not how it performs.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>2. Anonymous Posting by Default</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Safe space for real thoughts — especially the hard ones.</li>
          <li>Identity is optional. Honesty isn’t.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>3. Explore by Resonance</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Discover posts that reflect <em>your emotional state</em>, not
            what’s trending.
          </li>
          <li>AI groups emotional tone, not hashtags or clout.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>4. Monami – The Emotional AI</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Monami reads emotional patterns in your writing.</li>
          <li>
            Tracks moods, detects emotional states (e.g. anxiety, sadness,
            peace).
          </li>
          <li>Offers insights, soft prompts, and emotional reflections.</li>
          <li>It’s not therapy — it’s companionship with intelligence.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Core Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Anonymous / Identity toggle</li>
          <li>Explore tab powered by emotional filtering</li>
          <li>Monami (emotional analysis &amp; mood tracking)</li>
          <li>Daily journaling &amp; memory archive</li>
          <li>Minimalist, emotional design</li>
          <li>Dark/light mode (planned to auto-adjust to mood)</li>
          <li>Safe, secure data (private by default)</li>
          <li>
            Future: notifications based on <em>emotional relevance</em>, not
            activity
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Who Leads Ciphry?</h2>
        <blockquote>
          <strong>Cipherous</strong> – 17-year-old Ethiopian full stack
          developer, designer, and visionary.<br />
          Built Ciphry from scratch — from backend to front. Code, vision,
          design, voice — all you.
        </blockquote>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer>&copy; 2025 Ciphry &mdash; Built with heart by Cipherous</footer>
  </body>
</html>
